ce:section.ce:para:
For this study, CR, RhB and TC were selected as water-soluble organic pollutants for photocatalytic degradation experiments (

                        Fig. 1
                        ). Visible light irradiation was provided by a 300 W (XO-CHX-ID) Xe lamp with a cutoff filter (λ ≥ 420 nm) and the light intensity in the reactant center is around 25.6 mW/cm2. In a typical degradation procedure, 40 mg of catalysts was added into 40 ml of aqueous pollutants solution (CR, 120 mg L−1; RhB, 20 mg L−1; or TC, 80 mg L−1). And the solution was stirred for 30 min to acquire adsorption-desorption equilibrium. A small amount of the degraded solution was taken out at fixed intervals and centrifuged to remove the catalysts, then the UV–vis measurement was recorded for the supernatant.
